OL,6,FHe said both she and Gordon had a
OL,7,Fdistinctive odour that he associated
OL,8,Fwith homeless people.
OL,10,FThe officer's body-worn video showed
OL,11,Fthe moment they were arrested on
OL,12,Fsuspicion of child neglect.
OL,14,FMr Button approached Gordon and said:
OL,15,F"Hello. Sorry mate, can you stop for a
OL,16,Fsecond? Stop alright, I need to speak
OL,17,Fto you."
OL,19,FAsked what about, Mr Button said:
OL,20,F"Well because potentially I think you
OL,21,Fmay have been in the national news."
